Nineteen years ago, nearly 3,000 Americans lost their lives during the terrorist attacks on the World Trade Center, the Pentagon, and Flight 93.

Today, we take a moment to pause and reflect. We remember those we lost, the victims, the heroes, and the survivors. We will never forget.

OUTDOOR LEARNING EXPERIENCE
Lakeside students in Mrs. Hotho's Class had the opportunity to visit Garvan Woodland Gardens today for the inaugural Outdoor Learning Experience. Garvan Woodland Gardens has created a partnership with Lakeside and we couldn't be more excited. Students have various areas designated throughout the gardens where they can set up for outdoor learning. From classroom assignments to impromptu science lessons the students are provided endless learning opportunities.

Thank you, Garvan Woodland Gardens, for this wonderful opportunity. And shoutout to Mrs. Hotho for being our first CBI classroom to participate and enjoy!
.
.
.
Mrs. Hotho's Fabulous Class

#WeAreLakeside #GarvanWoodlandGardens #outsidethebox #outdoorlearning #outdoorclassroom

post_text:
Good news!

The USDA and Child Nutrition have extended the Seamless Summer Option meal waiver. This waiver allows all of our students to eat breakfast and lunch at no charge. Starting Thursday, Sept. 3, 2020, all Lakeside students can eat a school prepared breakfast and lunch at no cost. This waiver does not include the al la carte items. The waiver has only been extended until funding has been exhausted or December 31st, whichever comes first.

If you would like to come to the school to pick up meals, please fill out this form: https://forms.gle/3RFzgX8MjqkXcJQ99

For further information or questions, please email Mary_Webb@lakesidesd.org.

PAY-PER-VIEW & LAKESIDE HIGH SCHOOL STUDENT PRICING OPTIONS

Lakeside administration wants to guarantee that all high school students have the opportunity to watch athletic events at their normal ticket price, even though they may not be able to be physically present at the games. Lakeside High School students will be able to get Pay-Per-View games for $5 each with a promo code to be emailed them on Wednesday, August 26. This code will apply to the Senior Night Volleyball Game and/or the Lakeside-Lake Hamilton Football Game. The promo code must be used on Wednesday, August 26 to purchase discounted viewing options.

Volleyball Pay-Per-View Link - https://iframe.dacast.com/b/181428/c/562425

STUFF THE BUS United Way of the Ouachitas
This year, the Stuff the Bus School Supply Drive will be a virtual fundraiser! Due to the coronavirus pandemic and precautions to minimize contact, workplaces not yet at full capacity, and social distancing limiting large volunteer gatherings, we will be virtually supporting our students! In lieu of accepting school supply donations, we are raising money, so that school districts will have the necessary funds to purchase much-needed school supplies and technology for our students during this unconventional time.

Learn More: https://www.unitedwayouachitas.org/aboutstuffthebus

CERTIFIED TEACHING ASSISTANTS
We would like to congratulate, Lakeside‚Äôs first-ever Certified Teaching Assistants! These four students exceeded the list of requirements and are now qualified to be Teaching Assistants, and they are employable by a school district. We are so proud of these students.

Requirements:
-Pass the Praxis Paraprofessional Test
-Complete the concentrator pathway for Teaching and Training
-Have at least 80 hours of Field Experience (each of our students had 94 or more hours.)

#TeachArkansas #WeAreLakeside

Governor Asa Hutchinson announced the state would move back the start for the 2020-2021 school year.

The new dates for school districts to start classes will be between August 24 and 26.

Lakeside School District‚Äôs calendar committee will begin working on a new school calendar to meet the updated directives. Once the Lakeside School Board has approved the calendar, the School Calendar for 2020-2021 will be released.

LAKESIDE IS ON
During the 2020-2021 School Year, Lakeside is On. Onsite, online, or a combination; Lakeside will have options that fit your family‚Äôs circumstances. No matter what the future may hold, Lakeside will continue to provide your student with the best education possible.

If schools are open for onsite instruction, Lakeside will follow the directives and guidelines issued by the Arkansas Department of Health and the Division of Elementary and Secondary Education. In addition to onsite instruction, Lakeside will also be offering an online learning option (PreK-12) for families.

Continue to stay connected throughout the summer as we will be seeking input and feedback from our Lakeside families.

post_text:
A SPECIAL ZOOM | BRENT SOPEL
Friday, May 22nd, Mrs. Westerman held a special Zoom for her LHS students. Former NHL hockey professional, Brent Sopel, shared a little about his academic path, his love for hockey, and the struggles he faced along the way. Thank you, Brent, for spending time with our students and encouraging them, and thank you Mrs. Westerman for reaching out to provide this opportunity for our students.
--
Brent Sopel is a former NHL hockey professional who helped his team, the Chicago Blackhawks, win the Stanley Cup in 2010.

Brent has dyslexia and has a daughter who does too. He founded the Brent Sopel Foundation an organization to raise money for intervention and awareness for dyslexia.

Brent wants to help dyslexic students not only succeed academically but also to avoid pitfalls that he didn't.

Food Service Statement | Memorial Day Observance

Food Service Delivery/Pickup Schedule:
On Memorial Day, May 25th, Lakeside‚Äôs School District will be closed including our Food Service Delivery/Pickup in observance of Memorial Day.

On Friday, May 22nd, you will be provided 3 days of meals at no cost to children age 18 or younger for Friday, May 22nd, Monday, May 25th, and Tuesday, May 26th.

On Wednesday, May 27th, meal delivery/pickup will resume behind our Middle School at our regular schedule from 9:00 am to 12:00 pm.

We hope you have a wonderful Memorial Day weekend!

FOOD SERVICE DELIVERY & PICKUP SCHEDULE
Starting Monday, April 13th, 2020, Lakeside School District will start serving and delivering meals on Mondays, Wednesdays, and Fridays. Breakfast and Lunch will continue to be served at no cost to children age 18 or younger.

The meals being served will continue to be enough food to cover 5 days a week. These may be picked up behind Lakeside Middle School between 9:00 a.m. and 12:00 p.m.

Delivery & Pickup Schedule:
Monday: Mon & Tues Meals
Tues: No Pickup or Delivery
Wednesday: Wed‚Äôs & Thurs Meals
Thursday: No Pickup or Delivery
Friday: Friday Meals

If you‚Äôre unable to come to school to pick-up these meals, please call (501) 262-1880 and select ‚ÄúFood Service‚Äù to make arrangements.

DEADLINE FOR G&T NOMINATIONS: APRIL 3, 2020
Application: https://tinyurl.com/rprt2np

The Lakeside Gifted and Talented Education Program is accepting student nominations. Students who are currently in grades 3-12 may be nominated by parents, teachers, or community members. Lakeside offers enrichment classes for students who qualify in the 3rd, 4th and 5th grades along with extension opportunities in the higher grades.

ACADEMIC ABILITY:
High Standardized test scores (Nationally) and has well above average intelligence.

CREATIVE ABILITY:
Art, writing, music, exceptional thinking.

MOTIVATION:
Self-starter, independent worker, gets the job done, strong leadership skills.

Nominations are due by April 3, 2020. Any nominations received after that date will be considered in the fall.

Lakeside Rams Cafe
March 19 at 12:06 AM ¬∑

We want to express our heartfelt appreciation for all the comments, messages, phone calls, and kind words from everyone. When we got word on Sunday about the school closure we immediately started planning, organizing, and preparing for something we had never experienced. However, we have kept our 2 main goals in mind:
1. Get meals to the kids by any means necessary
2. Minimize contact to keep us, our school, and our community safe

Tuesday afternoon we were exhausted and worried if we were doing enough, but your feedback is the fuel that keeps us going! We are completely humbled by how many kids NEED and appreciate these meals.

We will continue to be here this week and now through spring break as well!
Pick up meals between 9am-12pm (or later if needed) behind LMS underneath the basketball goals.
If you do not have transportation to LMS please call 501-262-1880 and choose ‚Äúfood service‚Äù for delivery options.
üíôüíõüíôüíõ

Lakeside School District

post_text: Lakeside Intermediate School held its 3rd annual Mardi Gras Parade on Tuesday, February 25th. There were 110 2nd, 3rd, and 4th grade students that participated in the parade. Students helped design and make the floats in the parade. They also made homemade musical instruments and signs. There were 13 floats in the parade. Students that watched the parade caught beads, doubloons, TShirts, candy, and Mardi Gras cups. A good time was had by all!

Students helped design and make the floats in the parade. They also made homemade musical instruments and signs. There were 13 floats in the parade. post_text:
From Nurse Michelle at Lakeside Primary School:
We are starting to see some cases of flu at the school. Please remember if your child has a fever- they should not return to school until they have been fever free for twenty-four hours (and during that twenty-four hours they have not received ANY Tylenol or Ibuprofen). I appreciate your attention to this as it will prevent spreading the flu or other viruses.

Also, it has been really wet on the playground. My clothes closet is VERY low on clothes. If your child has received a change of clothes while at school, please wash them and return. If you have girls or boys pants size 4, 5, or 6 that you would like to donate, it would be greatly appreciated.
